    • writeArgs

      private static String writeArgs(Parameter[] parameters, boolean isImport)
      Generates a string of method arguments based on the supplied parameters.
      Parameters:
      parameters - an array of parameter objects representing the method parameters.
      isImport - a boolean value indicating whether to include parameter types or not. For example, if these are the arguments accepted by the method, then it is true, otherwise if we call the method and pass parameters to it, then false.
      Returns:
      a string representing the method arguments in the format "(arg1, arg2, ...)" or "(type1 arg1, type2 arg2, ...)".

    • getDefaultValue

      private static String getDefaultValue(Method method)
      Retrieves the default value for the return type of the provided Method object.
      Parameters:
      method - the Method object for which the default value is retrieved.
      Returns:
      a string representing the default value for the return type
      • if the return type is void, an EMPTY_STRING is returned.
      • if the return type is a primitive type, the appropriate default value (ZERO or FALSE) is returned.
      • if the return type is a reference type, NULL is returned.
